  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH response to COVID19 crisis to help vulnerable population in Eastern Ghouta, Dara&apos;a, Hama</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While WHO classifies Syria as a high-risk country with regard to COVID19, a first case was detected on the 22nd of March on the Syrian territory. Since then, the number of cases has been steadily increasing in a country where the health and medical infrastructures are hardly able to respond to the crisis without support from the humanitarian community. An estimated 6.8 million people live in communities with high population concentrations. In these communities, people often face limited access to water, health care, shelter, etc. These conditions increase the likelihood of transmission of COVID19 due to promiscuity. The risk of spread is heightened by the lack of access to basic hygiene products due to significant prices fluctuations that prevent households with low income to buy them. In addition to this already complex situation, there is a lack of awareness of protectives measures such as key handwashing moment and social distancing. 
In order to limit as much as possible the spread of the virus in a context where populations are extremely vulnerable, TGH will provide access to basic hygiene products and to water in sufficient quantity and quality so that everyone can meet their basic hygiene needs. Thus distributions of hygiene kits or soaps will be organized in the most vulnerable localities according to the needs assessment conducted by TGH in April 2020 in 3 governorates: Rural Damascus, Hama and Dara&#x2019;a. These distributions will be coupled with awareness sessions on safety measures such as handwashing key moments or social distancing in order to fill in the sometimes incomplete knowledge of the targeted populations on COVID19. Water trucking activities will be maintained so that people can access enough water to satisfy their basic needs. In total, 325,391 people will be reached by TGH proposed activities. For hygiene kit and soap distributions, the targeted localities will be covered in their entirety. Indeed, as this activity aims at preventing the spread of COVID19, the coverage should be total. Awareness messages will be delivered during distributions and will consequently also benefit the whole population of targeted villages. Similarly, water trucking services target the whole population in villages where the service is set up aligning with Do No Harm principles.</narrative>
  </description>
